	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yea, not bad, at least on my server, Shiny Brass Halberd is a newbie weapon given away or sold for like 50pp maybe.<br><br>Besides, value is only relative to those who use it. I have some nice armor and stuff, but i don't use it, and while i have it, it does nothing for me since i cant wear it, thus trading it for something i need, regardless of its street value means i got a good deal as it pertains to my needs. <br><br>Basically, you got a good/even deal for the halberd, which is only marginally better then a common drop velium two handed sword from Eastern wastes off almost any ulthork or rygorr orc there.<br><br>A good trade for you, you're getting there.<br><br>Heck i had only 140 wis at level 30, then i camped a few things and finally was able to make money in rathe mts and in ew at 35+ (and i have a friend who is a total fiend who plays like 14 hours a day and is now level 60, i helped him start out, so he takes care of me now:), but thats beside the point.<br><br>One key thing, if you haven't been told to camp the testament of vanear quest, then look into that, its a long camp, like 8-10 hours or so, depending upon when Darril Starshine(sp?) last spawned. Hes like level 16 or something, just have a friend help you camp him in High Pass Keep and do the quest related to him to get a +10 wis +10 book(which i still use and intend to for a LONG time).<br><br>But really, a good thing to do is ask around if someone has been hunting ulthorks and ask to buy a pair of ulthork bracers and one of the ulthork arms, the bracers are +1 wis each and +3 wis for the arms, and usually they are vendor fodder, so you could get all three pieces for like 25pp, heck cheaper.<br><br>Anyways, good luck, post back here if you have more questions<br><br>Kaj- lvl 44 dru of the rathe<br>(too lazy to spell out and capitalize)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
